{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Notebook 04 — Monitoring & Learning Agent\n",
    "\n",
    "Evaluates pricing decisions and runs a **simple feedback loop** that adjusts surge/discount multipliers.\n",
    "\n",
    "**OP'26 Metrics:**\n",
    "- Average Waiting Time Reduction\n",
    "- Customer Response Rate (demand elasticity proxy)\n",
    "- Pricing Efficiency Score (revenue per kWh)\n",
    "- Feedback loop performance over evaluation episodes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import json\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = Path.cwd().parent if Path.cwd().name == \"notebooks\" else Path.cwd()\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, str(PROJECT_ROOT))\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "import config\n",
    "from helpers.pricing import apply_dynamic_pricing_df, adjust_multipliers\n",
    "from helpers.metrics import (\n",
    "    monitoring_summary,\n",
    "    waiting_time_proxy,\n",
    "    pricing_efficiency_score,\n",
    "    customer_response_rate,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load tariff outcomes from Notebook 03\n",
    "pricing = pd.read_csv(config.TARIFFS_DIR / \"tariff_recommendations_test.csv\")\n",
    "pricing[\"datetime\"] = pd.to_datetime(pricing[\"datetime\"])\n",
    "print(\"Rows:\", len(pricing))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Monitoring Agent — Operational KPIs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "summary = monitoring_summary(pricing)\n",
    "summary_df = pd.DataFrame([summary]).T\n",
    "summary_df.columns = [\"value\"]\n",
    "print(\"=== Monitoring & Learning Agent — KPIs ===\")\n",
    "display(summary_df)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Waiting time proxy over peak hours\n",
    "pricing[\"hour\"] = pricing[\"datetime\"].dt.hour\n",
    "pricing[\"is_peak\"] = pricing[\"hour\"].between(7, 10) | pricing[\"hour\"].between(17, 20)\n",
    "\n",
    "peak = pricing[pricing[\"is_peak\"]].copy()\n",
    "peak[\"wait_before\"] = waiting_time_proxy(peak[\"actual_utilization\"])\n",
    "peak[\"wait_after\"] = waiting_time_proxy(peak[\"utilization_after\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Peak-hour avg wait proxy BEFORE: {peak['wait_before'].mean():.2f} min\")\n",
    "print(f\"Peak-hour avg wait proxy AFTER:  {peak['wait_after'].mean():.2f} min\")\n",
  ",
    "reduction = ((peak['wait_before'].mean() - peak['wait_after'].mean()) / max(peak['wait_before'].mean(), 1e-9)) * 100\n",
    "print(f\"Average Waiting Time Reduction (peak): {reduction:.2f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Customer Response Rate (Demand Elasticity Proxy)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for tier in [\"surge\", \"discount\", \"standard\"]:\n",
    "    subset = pricing[pricing[\"pricing_tier\"] == tier]\n",
    "    if len(subset) == 0:\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "    resp = customer_response_rate(subset[\"volume_kwh\"].mean(), subset[\"volume_after\"].mean())\n",
    "    print(f\"{tier:10s} — customer response rate: {resp:+.2f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Pricing Efficiency Over Time\n",
    "Revenue per kWh — does the system improve across evaluation episodes?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pricing[\"date\"] = pricing[\"datetime\"].dt.date\n",
    "daily = pricing.groupby(\"date\").agg(\n",
    "    revenue_fixed=(\"revenue_fixed_inr\", \"sum\"),\n",
    "    revenue_dynamic=(\"revenue_dynamic_inr\", \"sum\"),\n",
    "    volume_kwh=(\"volume_kwh\", \"sum\"),\n",
    ").reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "daily[\"efficiency_fixed\"] = daily[\"revenue_fixed\"] / daily[\"volume_kwh\"].replace(0, np.nan)\n",
    "daily[\"efficiency_dynamic\"] = daily[\"revenue_dynamic\"] / daily[\"volume_kwh\"].replace(0, np.nan)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 4))\n",
    "ax.plot(daily[\"date\"], daily[\"efficiency_fixed\"], label=\"Fixed ₹15/kWh\", marker=\"o\")\n",
    "ax.plot(daily[\"date\"], daily[\"efficiency_dynamic\"], label=\"Dynamic pricing\", marker=\"s\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Pricing Efficiency Score (Revenue per kWh) Over Time\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Date\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"INR per kWh\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Learning Feedback Loop\n",
    "The Monitoring Agent adjusts pricing multipliers based on outcomes — **not RL**, just transparent rule updates."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Simulate multiple evaluation episodes (weekly chunks of test data)\n",
    "pricing = pricing.sort_values(\"datetime\")\n",
    "pricing[\"week\"] = pricing[\"datetime\"].dt.isocalendar().week.astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "surge_mult = config.SURGE_MULTIPLIER\n",
    "discount_mult = config.DISCOUNT_MULTIPLIER\n",
    "learning_log = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for week in sorted(pricing[\"week\"].unique()):\n",
    "    episode = pricing[pricing[\"week\"] == week].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Re-apply pricing with current multipliers\n",
    "    episode = apply_dynamic_pricing_df(\n",
    "        episode,\n",
    "        surge_mult=surge_mult,\n",
    "        discount_mult=discount_mult,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    rev_fixed = episode[\"revenue_fixed_inr\"].sum()\n",
    "    rev_dyn = episode[\"revenue_dynamic_inr\"].sum()\n",
    "    gain = ((rev_dyn - rev_fixed) / max(rev_fixed, 1e-9)) * 100\n",
    "    congestion = (episode[\"actual_utilization\"] >= 0.80).mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "    surge_mult, discount_mult, reason = adjust_multipliers(gain, congestion, surge_mult, discount_mult)\n",
    "\n",
    "    learning_log.append({\n",
    "        \"week\": week,\n",
    "        \"revenue_gain_pct\": round(gain, 2),\n",
    "        \"congestion_rate\": round(congestion, 3),\n",
    "        \"surge_multiplier\": round(surge_mult, 3),\n",
    "        \"discount_multiplier\": round(discount_mult, 3),\n",
    "        \"adjustment_reason\": reason,\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "learning_df = pd.DataFrame(learning_log)\n",
    "display(learning_df)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 4))\n",
    "ax1.plot(learning_df[\"week\"], learning_df[\"revenue_gain_pct\"], \"b-o\", label=\"Revenue Gain %\")\n",
    "ax1.set_xlabel(\"Week (episode)\")\n",
    "ax1.set_ylabel(\"Revenue Gain %\", color=\"b\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax2 = ax1.twinx()\n",
    "ax2.plot(learning_df[\"week\"], learning_df[\"surge_multiplier\"], \"r--s\", label=\"Surge Mult\")\n",
    "ax2.plot(learning_df[\"week\"], learning_df[\"discount_multiplier\"], \"g--^\", label=\"Discount Mult\")\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel(\"Multiplier\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax1.set_title(\"Monitoring Agent: Learning Loop Over Episodes\")\n",
    "fig.legend(loc=\"upper right\", bbox_to_anchor=(0.88, 0.88))\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Final Agent Summary (for submission CSV)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "final_report = {\n",
    "    **summary,\n",
    "    \"final_surge_multiplier\": surge_mult,\n",
    "    \"final_discount_multiplier\": discount_mult,\n",
    "    \"peak_waiting_reduction_pct\": round(reduction, 2),\n",
    "    \"learning_episodes\": len(learning_df),\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(config.REPORTS_DIR / \"monitoring_agent_report.json\", \"w\") as f:\n",
    "    json.dump(final_report, f, indent=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "learning_df.to_csv(config.REPORTS_DIR / \"learning_loop_log.csv\", index=False)\n",
    "pd.DataFrame([final_report]).to_csv(config.REPORTS_DIR / \"monitoring_agent_summary.csv\", index=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"All monitoring outputs saved to\", config.REPORTS_DIR)\n",
    "print(\"\\n=== PIPELINE COMPLETE ===\")\n",
    "print(\"Run notebooks 01 → 02 → 03 → 04 in order for full reproducibility.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Limitations (include in presentation — OP'26 asks for transparency)\n",
    "\n",
    "1. UrbanEV (Shenzhen) and ACN (Caltech) are **not merged** on station ID — different networks.\n",
    "2. Demand response after tariff changes is **simulated** via elasticity assumptions, not observed causal data.\n",
    "3. ₹15/kWh baseline is applied per problem statement; UrbanEV `price_index` is a relative tariff signal.\n",
    "4. Queue/wait times use a **proxy**, not real queue observations.\n",
    "5. The learning loop adjusts multipliers with simple rules — not reinforcement learning."
   ]
  }
 ],
